reviews.review: It was definitely more of a Star Wars movie than The Last Jedi. I hated The Last Jedi passionately. The Rise of Skywalker definitely had a lot of fan service at the end but overall good. It had the Star Wars feel that was severely lacking in the last movie. If you loved the last one you'll probably hate this one. As a huge fan of the original movies and the Expanded Universe books I feel like this was the best that could be done after Rian Johnson screwed up the new Trilogy so badly.
Great save by JJ. Star Wars is back to being Star Wars!

A nonsensical plot surrounding boring characters and poor decisions. If you want a popcorn flick devoid of cohesive storytelling and don't mind characters teleporting around a universe in search of a way to get to a hidden villain hiding for no reason, then this for you. Disney, JJ and Rian all complain that the old school fan just cant accept their character choices. And, while that may be true, the fact is that these are just not well plotted movies with a story that makes any sense at all. Why should the audience care about what they are seeing because Fisney Wars has given zero reason beyond, "because Star Wars."

The worst, most insulting Star Wars movie to date. The movie spits in the face of loyal fans to appeal to the mainstream audience. Its only accomplishment is somehow making The Last Jedi come off as a superior movie. The rushed, lazy, and predictable plot allow for the middling action scenes to be the only reprieve from the urge to walk right out of the theater. Deplorable movie, wouldn't wish its viewing on my worst enemy.
I thought it was a great end to the saga. I am a huge star wars fan, but my wife and dad arnt but they enjoyed the movie too.
Pretty convoluted plot which was necessary to correct the dumpster fire left by The Last Jedi.
Totally enjoyed the movie.  It was so well done and there were several surprise areas.  I know I will see it several more time.
Rushed and shallow storytelling. Focused more on undoing Johnson's directions without exposition and giving the fans little winks than it did on character development and a story that made any sense.

Any true Star Wars fan will love this. A rollercoaster of emotions. Great adventure, characters we care for, music, sound, amazing effects.  Waited my whole life for this. I might of done things differently myself but it is what it is and it is awesome. Can't wait for more Star Wars spin offs that are coming soon, so many adventures in an amazing Universe. Born in the 70s I grew up with the originals, which will always be the best but the prequels and the sequels are still excellent trilogy's in there own right. Loved every second.

I thought it was much better than the last 2.  I had low expectations which were exceeded. Not sure how the reviews have been so bad for this film, but I enjoyed it. Should have had JJ Abrams direct all 3 tbh and the trilogy would have been a lot better overall.
